io.github.nixtabyte.telegram.jtelebot.server.impl

Class DefaultCommandWatcher

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.github.nixtabyte.telegram.jtelebot.server.impl.AbstractCommandWatcher
      • io.github.nixtabyte.telegram.jtelebot.server.impl.DefaultCommandWatcher
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    CommandWatcher, Service, Runnable

    public class DefaultCommandWatcher
extends AbstractCommandWatcher
    Main implementation of CommandWatcher that extends the AbstractCommandWatcher behavior in order to implement a polling component service for the Telegram Bot API service. This is a watcher that is continuously observing when there are commands available, which are originated by a Telegram User.

    It has a reference to a CommandDispatcher implementation so that it can bypass via its queue, the group of Command instances collected on every bunch of polling updates.

    For the polling purpose, it uses a DefaultRequestHandler implementation internally in order to send requests to the Telegram Bot API service and get Updates as the result.
    Since:
    0.0.1
    See Also:
    Command, CommandWatcher, AbstractCommandWatcher, CommandDispatcher, DefaultRequestHandler, Update
